218
00:11:13,300 --> 00:11:16,371
From your first fart
to your last dying breath.

219
00:11:16,406 --> 00:11:19,006
- ( chuckles )
- You think it's funny?

220
00:11:19,039 --> 00:11:21,442
I apologize deeply.

221
00:11:21,476 --> 00:11:23,378
What happened?

222
00:11:23,412 --> 00:11:25,345
Let me ask you, Peggy.

223
00:11:25,379 --> 00:11:27,545
- You ever heard of Underdog?
- The cartoon?

224
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,714
Yeah.
Sweet Polly Purebred.

225
00:11:29,749 --> 00:11:31,183
Saturday morning.

226
00:11:31,217 --> 00:11:33,119
It makes hundreds of thousands
of dollars a year.

227
00:11:33,153 --> 00:11:36,555
Mostly for its creator Chet
Stover of Dancer Fitzgerald.

228
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:39,225
- Did you know him there?
- He was nothing special.

229
00:11:39,259 --> 00:11:41,794
"Scout's Honor"
is 100 times better.

230
00:11:41,828 --> 00:11:45,025
I can tell you right now,
it's a winner.

231
00:11:46,461 --> 00:11:49,695
You know who had a ridiculous
dream and people laughed at him?

232
00:11:49,729 --> 00:11:53,127
- You?
- ( laughs )

233
00:11:53,162 --> 00:11:54,829
What?

234
00:11:54,863 --> 00:11:57,533
Oh, I did not mean that
the way it sounded.

235
00:11:57,567 --> 00:12:01,070
I mean, if you're telling us
that this is your dream,

236
00:12:01,104 --> 00:12:04,271
I apologize for being one
of those naysaying idiots.

237
00:12:04,306 --> 00:12:05,739
I hate people like that.

238
00:12:07,342 --> 00:12:09,476
Bob Dylan.

239
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:11,214
Is he hip enough for you?

240
00:12:11,248 --> 00:12:13,549
He was 20 years old when he
wrote "Blowin' in the Wind"

241
00:12:13,584 --> 00:12:15,617
and he's a genius.

242
00:12:15,651 --> 00:12:17,985
Look at where he is,
look at where you are.

243
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:19,788
( stifled laugh )

244
00:12:19,823 --> 00:12:21,491
You know what?

245
00:12:21,526 --> 00:12:24,026
You're a bunch of
flag-burning snots.

246
00:12:24,060 --> 00:12:27,428
You've got a thing to learn
about patriotism and loyalty.

247
00:12:27,462 --> 00:12:30,534
The very fabric of "Scout's
Honor" is a joke to you.

248
00:12:32,036 --> 00:12:33,636
We're gonna have
this meeting later.

249
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:36,775
So order dinner because
I want finished work.

250
00:12:38,078 --> 00:12:39,478
And if any of you
don't like it,

251
00:12:39,513 --> 00:12:42,012
