Put me on that.

253
00:13:01,466 --> 00:13:04,066
- I'll cancel my plans.
- Just mine, not yours.

254
00:13:05,634 --> 00:13:07,300
I don't know if it's vandals

255
00:13:07,335 --> 00:13:09,236
or just kids being kids.

256
00:13:09,270 --> 00:13:10,804
What is it?

257
00:13:10,839 --> 00:13:13,340
Someone broke all the
streetlights on Peck Avenue.

258
00:13:13,374 --> 00:13:15,040
And you want Henry
to get them fixed?

259
00:13:15,075 --> 00:13:18,109
No. Mike was just saying
it's a national disease.

260
00:13:18,143 --> 00:13:20,077
The wildness of the kids.

261
00:13:20,111 --> 00:13:21,945
I just don't expect it
in Westchester.

262
00:13:21,979 --> 00:13:25,114
I know all everyone wants
to talk about is Vietnam,

263
00:13:25,148 --> 00:13:28,384
but things are
falling apart here, too.

264
00:13:28,419 --> 00:13:30,451
The rumaki is exquisite.

265
00:13:30,485 --> 00:13:32,452
Thank you.

266
00:13:32,487 --> 00:13:35,324
Well, I don't know, that
those things are unrelated.

267
00:13:35,359 --> 00:13:38,159
I mean, first the kids
start off protesting

268
00:13:38,193 --> 00:13:41,197
and the next thing you know every
authority is up for grabs.

269
00:13:41,231 --> 00:13:43,933
I mean, if they learned
how to support their country,

270
00:13:43,967 --> 00:13:46,967
sacrifice in hard times, we'd
have the morale to win the war.

271
00:13:47,002 --> 00:13:49,804
Mike, you have plans
for the summer?

272
00:13:49,839 --> 00:13:52,509
Even Nixon wants to bring
the war to an end.

273
00:13:52,544 --> 00:13:54,344
I'm surprised, Henry.

274
00:13:54,379 --> 00:13:56,747
Don't be, Mike.
I agree with Nixon.

275
00:13:56,781 --> 00:13:58,948
I think it's too costly.

276
00:13:58,983 --> 00:14:00,717
It has to be done
on the right terms,

277
00:14:00,751 --> 00:14:02,652
but I think we should get out
while the getting's good.

278
00:14:02,686 --> 00:14:04,352
Since when?

279
00:14:04,386 --> 00:14:06,854
I've always supported
the president, honey.

280
00:14:09,792 --> 00:14:12,331
I think that maybe everyone
should fill up here.

281
00:14:12,365 --> 00:14:14,701
I don't know
if my lamb turned out.

282
00:14:14,735 --> 00:14:16,636
I'm sure it's delicious.

283
00:14:16,670 --> 00:14:18,771
Let me check the Sterno.

284
00:14:24,008 --> 00:14:25,576
( knocks )

285
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:30,115
Well, I think I worked
every side of the strategy.

286
00:14:31,586 --> 00:14:33,657
Don, you've been the boss.

287
00:14:33,691 --> 00:14:36,994
The briefcase and the hat,
that's a rookie maneuver.

288
00:14:37,029 --> 00:14:38,696
You got someplace to be?

289
00:14:38,730 --> 00:14:41,029
I'm afraid I do.

290
00:14:41,063 --> 00:14:43,233
How's it going to look
for them if I let you go?

291
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:44,835
Well, you could let
everybody go.

292
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:46,337
Is that what you would do?

293
00:14:46,371 --> 00:14:49,074
No, I'd let<i> you</i> go, Lou.

294
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:53,145
Well, I'm afraid
it's too late for that.

295
00:14:53,179 --> 00:14:56,314
I'm gonna do you the
courtesy of reading these

296
00:14:56,348 --> 00:14:59,650
so that you can continue to work on them
instead of coming up with new things,

297
00:14:59,684 --> 00:15:02,153
because I'm gonna
tuck you in tonight.

298
00:15:05,958 --> 00:15:07,658
About your cartoon.

299
00:15:07,693 --> 00:15:09,626
Here we go.

300
00:15:09,660 --> 00:15:12,828
This is an office made out of people
who have problems with authority.

301
00:15:12,862 --> 00:15:15,597
You know you have to have a thick
skin, but don't help them.

302
00:15:15,631 --> 00:15:19,067
I'm not taking management
advice from Don Draper.

303
00:15:23,873 --> 00:15:26,174
( phone ringing )

304
00:15:28,212 --> 00:15:29,780
Hello.

305
00:15:29,814 --> 00:15:31,848
I can't get out
of here tonight.

306
00:15:31,883 --> 00:15:34,182
Oh, I'm sorry.

307
00:15:34,216 --> 00:15:37,153
- Is she there yet?
- She's taking a bath.

308
00:15:37,188 --> 00:15:38,389
How is she?

309
00:15:38,423 --> 00:15:40,158
She's pretty far along.

310
00:15:40,193 --> 00:15:42,963
So beautiful.

311
00:15:42,997 --> 00:15:46,335
Well, don't bother her. Tell her
I'll see her in the morning.

312
00:15:46,370 --> 00:15:48,374
Don't worry.
I made her a steak.

313
00:15:48,408 --> 00:15:50,075
Thank you.

314
00:15:54,243 --> 00:15:56,444
Okay, I'll see you
tomorrow morning.

315
00:15:56,479 --> 00:15:57,813
Okay.

316
00:15:59,783 --> 00:16:01,850
Damn, that smells good.

317
00:16:03,622 --> 00:16:06,089
Don's stuck in New York. He's
flying in tomorrow morning.

318
00:16:06,124 --> 00:16:08,324
Was that him?

319
00:16:08,359 --> 00:16:11,029
Yeah, he's frustrated.
I told him not to worry.

320
00:16:12,566 --> 00:16:14,268
Wait, do you want
to eat outside?

321
00:16:14,303 --> 00:16:16,636
I do that all the time.

322
00:16:20,038 --> 00:16:21,739
I love that you're
wearing Anna's ring.

323
00:16:21,774 --> 00:16:24,244
Oh, yes.
It's beautiful.

324
00:16:26,548 --> 00:16:28,514
I'm sorry I never met her.

325
00:16:28,549 --> 00:16:30,750
She's around.
Believe me, you've met her.

326
00:16:30,785 --> 00:16:32,920
She's happy it's in the family.

327
00:16:32,954 --> 00:16:36,155
Well, maybe you'll have
someone there to give it to.

328
00:16:36,189 --> 00:16:38,123
Oh, no.
It's yours now

329
00:16:38,158 --> 00:16:39,825
You'll probably have
someone of your own.

330
00:16:39,859 --> 00:16:42,731
We'll see.
I don't know.

331
00:16:42,765 --> 00:16:45,468
Don's kids are plenty for me.

332
00:16:45,502 --> 00:16:47,371
( sighs )

333
00:16:47,405 --> 00:16:49,307
I haven't eaten meat in a year.

334
00:16:49,342 --> 00:16:51,276
I don't think
this is a good idea.

335
00:16:51,311 --> 00:16:53,142
I can make spaghetti.

336
00:16:54,643 --> 00:16:57,446
It's probably hard
with you here and him there.

337
00:16:59,016 --> 00:17:00,850
Are you with someone?

338
00:17:00,884 --> 00:17:04,052
Not right now.
He was a musician.

339
00:17:04,086 --> 00:17:05,687
They're the worst.

340
00:17:05,722 --> 00:17:08,860
Dropped out of school.
Followed him down here.

341
00:17:08,894 --> 00:17:10,962
Started flush at the beach,

342
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:13,632
ended up downtown panhandling.

343
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:16,506
And then he got busted
dealing grass

344
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:19,275
and we celebrated
before he went away.

345
00:17:19,309 --> 00:17:21,611
He'll be out in a month.

346
00:17:21,646 --> 00:17:24,549
So will this little guy.

347
00:17:24,583 --> 00:17:26,217
Does he know?

348
00:17:26,251 --> 00:17:27,585
No.

349
00:17:27,619 --> 00:17:29,953
I'm afraid he'd murder
someone just to stay in jail.

350
00:17:31,521 --> 00:17:33,889
- I won't tell Don.
- Oh, I don't care.

351
00:17:33,923 --> 00:17:35,624
I know all of his secrets.

352
00:17:41,898 --> 00:17:44,899
But you don't
know<i> him</i> very well.

353
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:47,633
You're right.
You're right.

354
00:17:49,469 --> 00:17:51,503
It's just I'm looking at you

355
00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:54,504
and seeing how, well,
disorganized this all is.

356
00:17:54,539 --> 00:17:56,105
And I don't think
he'd stand for that.

357
00:17:56,140 --> 00:17:59,543
I don't think he'd trust you
to make your own plans.

358
00:18:01,714 --> 00:18:04,349
I don't know what I'm doing here.
This is a dumb idea.

359
00:18:04,383 --> 00:18:07,587
No, no, I mean,
he wants to help,

360
00:18:07,621 --> 00:18:10,521
I'm sure, in his way.
We both do.

361
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:25,033
I'm going to give you...

362
00:18:26,969 --> 00:18:29,671
would $1,000
get you far enough?

363
00:18:29,706 --> 00:18:32,507
That's very generous.

364
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:35,009
This comes with no strings.

365
00:18:36,777 --> 00:18:38,676
Thank you.

366
00:18:42,015 --> 00:18:44,883
I really think
it's better this way.

367
00:18:44,917 --> 00:18:48,054
You're right.
I'm gonna take off.

368
00:18:48,088 --> 00:18:49,589
You haven't eaten anything yet.

369
00:18:49,623 --> 00:18:52,723
I guess I got what I came for.

370
00:18:52,758 --> 00:18:54,359
There's no rush.

371
00:18:57,330 --> 00:18:59,701
Nothing ever happened
between us, you know.

372
00:18:59,736 --> 00:19:01,904
Of course not.

373
00:19:01,939 --> 00:19:04,938
You're his niece.
I know that.

374
00:19:17,495 --> 00:19:18,863
( door slams )

375
00:19:18,898 --> 00:19:20,399
The children are asleep.

376
00:19:20,434 --> 00:19:23,570
- What about your headache?
- Keep your voice down.

377
00:19:23,604 --> 00:19:25,473
I did not appreciate going stag

378
00:19:25,507 --> 00:19:28,109
to four people's homes
whom I barely know.

379
00:19:28,144 --> 00:19:31,448
I'm sorry. I wasn't feeling well.
You didn't have to go.

380
00:19:33,018 --> 00:19:34,784
Hey, "Emily Post."

381
00:19:34,819 --> 00:19:36,785
Why were you
talking about the war?

382
00:19:36,819 --> 00:19:38,617
I didn't bring it up.

383
00:19:38,651 --> 00:19:40,851
But maybe I should more because
I didn't know where you stood.

384
00:19:40,886 --> 00:19:42,253
I shouldn't have to brief you

385
00:19:42,287 --> 00:19:44,622
because you shouldn't be
talking about those things.

386
00:19:44,656 --> 00:19:46,390
I'm not a dinner companion.

387
00:19:46,424 --> 00:19:47,791
I'm their elected
representative.

388
00:19:47,825 --> 00:19:50,492
- You ran unopposed.
- We'll see if that lasts.

389
00:19:50,527 --> 00:19:52,593
From now on, keep your
conversation to how much you hate

390
00:19:52,627 --> 00:19:55,529
getting toast crumbs in the butter
and leave the thinking to me.

391
00:19:58,401 --> 00:20:01,201
Henry!

392
00:20:01,236 --> 00:20:03,338
I'm sorry. It just
caught me off-guard.

393
00:20:03,373 --> 00:20:06,475
Well, you embarrassed
yourself way more than me.

394
00:20:10,747 --> 00:20:12,717
<i>( door slams )</i>

395
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,953
You know what?

396
00:20:20,987 --> 00:20:23,289
I decided I can
see that Monday.

397
00:20:24,823 --> 00:20:26,721
Good night.

398
00:20:37,701 --> 00:20:40,436
( phone ringing )

399
00:20:44,241 --> 00:20:45,942
Hello.

400
00:20:45,976 --> 00:20:48,375
What?

401
00:20:52,181 --> 00:20:54,546
Is she okay?

402
00:20:54,581 --> 00:20:56,747
( water running )

403
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,722
Hello?

404
00:21:02,757 --> 00:21:04,090
Oh, hi.

405
00:21:06,360 --> 00:21:08,227
- Who are you?
- I'm Amy.

406
00:21:08,262 --> 00:21:10,896
- We met on the phone.
- Is Megan here?

407
00:21:10,931 --> 00:21:13,198
Oh, Don.
I...

408
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:15,000
Amy, do you mind?

409
00:21:15,034 --> 00:21:17,604
I'll just use the ladies'.

410
00:21:20,841 --> 00:21:23,775
I'm sorry, but she left.

411
00:21:23,809 --> 00:21:25,880
You told her
I wanted to see her?

412
00:21:25,914 --> 00:21:27,517
I really tried
to get her to stay.

413
00:21:27,551 --> 00:21:29,819
But the money already came up

414
00:21:29,853 --> 00:21:31,551
and I gave her $1,000.

415
00:21:31,586 --> 00:21:33,520
She must have been embarrassed.

416
00:21:33,554 --> 00:21:35,722
She said she'd call
you from Oakland.

417
00:21:35,757 --> 00:21:38,158
You should have called me.
At least let me talk to her.

418
00:21:38,193 --> 00:21:40,262
She's an adult, Don.

419
00:21:44,734 --> 00:21:46,601
Do you want to go
to the market with us?

420
00:21:46,635 --> 00:21:48,669
You know, I'm gonna
have company tonight.

421
00:21:48,703 --> 00:21:50,337
Maybe it'll cheer you up.

422
00:21:52,839 --> 00:21:55,140
We'll go.
Amy.

423
00:21:57,676 --> 00:22:00,579
- Is everything okay?
- Yes.

424
00:22:00,613 --> 00:22:02,848
- We should go.
- Anything for you, Don?

425
00:22:02,882 --> 00:22:05,251
I know what he likes.

426
00:22:09,291 --> 00:22:11,392
<i>( computer humming )</i>

427
00:22:12,394 --> 00:22:14,596
<i>( humming continues )</i>

428
00:22:17,870 --> 00:22:19,838
( clears throat )

429
00:22:31,055 --> 00:22:33,390
<i>( muffled humming )</i>

430
00:22:35,758 --> 00:22:37,723
( sighs )

431
00:22:52,436 --> 00:22:54,870
( no audible dialogue )

432
00:23:14,087 --> 00:23:16,086
We're back.

433
00:23:18,689 --> 00:23:21,058
- Let me see.
- She's fine.

434
00:23:21,093 --> 00:23:22,725
Couple of black eyes.

435
00:23:24,027 --> 00:23:26,994
Ow.
Can I go lie down?

436
00:23:27,028 --> 00:23:28,795
I want to know
what really happened.

437
00:23:28,830 --> 00:23:31,096
They were sword fighting
with golf clubs.

438
00:23:31,130 --> 00:23:33,600
- We're idiots, okay?
- You are.

439
00:23:33,635 --> 00:23:35,337
You can't be
trusted on your own.

440
00:23:35,371 --> 00:23:36,572
That's your face, young lady.

441
00:23:36,607 --> 00:23:38,475
That's right, it's<i> my</i> face.

442
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:41,880
- Why am I even here?
- Girls! Girls! Please.

443
00:23:41,914 --> 00:23:45,419
Sally, you can understand how your mother
and I are both worried about your nose.

444
00:23:45,453 --> 00:23:48,790
Yeah, I know, because where would
Mom be without her perfect nose?

445
00:23:48,824 --> 00:23:50,794
She wouldn't find
a man like you.

446
00:23:50,828 --> 00:23:52,697
She'd be nothing.

447
00:23:52,732 --> 00:23:55,000
It<i> was</i> a perfect nose.

448
00:23:55,034 --> 00:23:56,766
And<i> I</i> gave it to you.

449
00:23:56,801 --> 00:23:58,770
You're lucky Henry
is important enough

450
00:23:58,805 --> 00:24:00,806
to get Dr. Kramer
to fix it this weekend.

451
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:03,376
I suppose you'd rather do
it in a barn in Farmington.

452
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:05,745
It's a nose job,
not an abortion.

453
00:24:05,779 --> 00:24:08,447
- I'm going to break your arm next.
- Betty!

454
00:24:08,481 --> 00:24:10,181
Don't worry about me
finding a man.

455
00:24:10,214 --> 00:24:12,215
I already have you
to keep me in line.

456
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:15,119
You're going to your room and you're
going to wait there until morning.

457
00:24:15,154 --> 00:24:17,487
Good, I prefer it.

458
00:24:31,296 --> 00:24:32,899
Hello.

459
00:24:32,933 --> 00:24:34,866
Just a minute.

460
00:24:34,901 --> 00:24:36,433
It's for Megan again.

461
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:38,868
Megan?

462
00:24:38,903 --> 00:24:41,037
It's Greenblatt's.

463
00:24:43,538 --> 00:24:44,737
Hello.

464
00:24:44,771 --> 00:24:46,772
<i>( knock on door )</i>

465
00:24:52,779 --> 00:24:55,581
The main door was open and you
didn't check the peephole?

466
00:24:55,615 --> 00:24:56,849
It's a bad neighborhood.

467
00:24:56,884 --> 00:24:58,084
What are you doing here?

468
00:24:58,118 --> 00:24:59,851
I wanted to tell you--

469
00:24:59,885 --> 00:25:01,752
May I?

470
00:25:01,786 --> 00:25:03,421
Michael.

471
00:25:03,456 --> 00:25:05,859
I was just in the office and
there's something going on.

472
00:25:05,893 --> 00:25:07,495
- What?
- The computer.

473
00:25:07,530 --> 00:25:10,529
It's Saturday.
Take the day off.

474
00:25:10,564 --> 00:25:12,663
That's right. So why
were Lou and Cutler

475
00:25:12,698 --> 00:25:14,731
having a secret meeting in
that air-conditioned lair?

476
00:25:14,765 --> 00:25:17,637
- I don't know.
- But I do.

477
00:25:17,671 --> 00:25:19,206
They're homos.

478
00:25:19,240 --> 00:25:21,175
( chuckles )
Okay.

479
00:25:21,209 --> 00:25:22,909
Anything else to report?

480
00:25:22,944 --> 00:25:24,444
Peggy, it's serious.

481
00:25:24,478 --> 00:25:26,648
That machine makes men
do unnatural things.

482
00:25:26,682 --> 00:25:28,084
What did you see?

483
00:25:28,118 --> 00:25:29,853
( knocks )

484
00:25:33,057 --> 00:25:34,725
- Who are you?
- This is Julio.

485
00:25:34,759 --> 00:25:36,730
- Hello.
- Hey.

486
00:25:36,764 --> 00:25:39,331
I'd like to say Peggy's mentioned
you at work, but she hasn't.

487
00:25:39,365 --> 00:25:41,166
Julio lives upstairs.

488
00:25:41,199 --> 00:25:43,935
Interesting arrangement.
Very modern.

489
00:25:43,970 --> 00:25:45,373
I live with my mama.

490
00:25:45,407 --> 00:25:47,076
I live with my pop,

491
00:25:47,110 --> 00:25:48,778
which is why I can't
work at home.

492
00:25:48,812 --> 00:25:51,146
Can I please work here?
I can't go back to the office.

493
00:25:51,180 --> 00:25:53,016
Not right now.
I'll stay out of your way.

494
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:56,686
Fine.

495
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,086
Can I use your typewriter?

496
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:00,122
It's too loud.

497
00:26:09,564 --> 00:26:11,331
<i>( TV playing )</i>

498
00:26:13,420 --> 00:26:15,788
<i>( "You've Made Me</i>
<i>So Very Happy" playing )</i>

499
00:26:15,822 --> 00:26:17,988
( guests chatting )

500
00:26:18,022 --> 00:26:20,387
<i>♪ you've treated me so kind ♪</i>

501
00:26:20,421 --> 00:26:23,053
<i>♪ I'm about to lose my mind ♪</i>

502
00:26:23,088 --> 00:26:27,789
<i>♪ you make me so very happy ♪</i>

503
00:26:27,824 --> 00:26:30,791
<i>♪ I'm so glad you ♪</i>

504
00:26:30,826 --> 00:26:32,626
<i>♪ came into my life... ♪</i>

505
00:26:32,660 --> 00:26:35,126
I wouldn't have invited
them both if I had known.

506
00:26:35,161 --> 00:26:37,530
I swear, I thought she
was his daughter.

507
00:26:37,564 --> 00:26:40,202
Don't you kind of want
